# Cpmech presentation template

cpmech Presentation Template using RevealJS and Jstar

## Installation

If you have the developer tools installed installed (see below), you can simply install the required dependencies with the following commands:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/cpmech/presentation.git
cd presentation
npm install jspm@beta --save-dev
jspm install
```

## Writing your presentation

Three files are required to type in your presentation:

1. index.html
2. src/presentation.js
3. src/configuration.js

If you're not using Plotxy, make sure to clear the file *src/presentation.js*.

File *src/configuration.js* allows you to set RevealJS as explained here: https://github.com/hakimel/reveal.js/

## Running your presentation

```bash
npm run serve
```

## Install tools if not available (first time)

```bash
sudo apt-get install nodejs-legacy npm
sudo npm install -g browser-sync jspm@beta
```

## How to create a new JSPM package (dev setup)
```
jspm init
jspm install github:hakimel/reveal.js
jspm install github:cpmech/jstar
```
